    [Australia] [has] [dipl. rels.]
    [with North Korea]2 [is]1 [one of the few countries] [.] where we have used subscripts to indicate the reordering of phrases.
    The phrase-based model is able to order &#8220;has diplomatic relations with North Korea&#8221; correctly (using phrase reordering) and &#8220;is one of the few countries&#8221; correctly (using a combination of phrase translation and phrase reordering), but does not invert these two groups as it should.
